documentation.title: Geocoding
documentation.description: Code or decode a postal address to or from geographical coordinates.

documentation.title: Geocode address
documentation.description: Geocode a postal address into geographical coordinates (latitude and longitude).

value.value: Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, United States of America
The provided coordinates in query are invalid, out of range, or not in the expected format

documentation.title: Reverse geocode
documentation.description: Decodes geographical coordinates (latitude and longitude) into a postal address.

documentation.title: Query
documentation.description: Free-form query string to search for. For example, '1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA' or just 'Mountain View'

documentation.title: Country
documentation.description: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

documentation.title: Region
documentation.description: The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level Administrative division.

documentation.title: Locality
documentation.description: The locality in which the street address is, and which is in the region. For example, Mountain View.

documentation.title: Street address
documentation.description: The street address. For example, 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy.

documentation.title: Latitude
documentation.description: The latitude of a location. For example 37.42242 (WGS 84).

documentation.title: Longitude
documentation.description: The longitude of a location. For example -122.08585 (WGS 84).

documentation.title: Title
documentation.description: A short, human-readable summary of the problem type.

documentation.title: Detail
documentation.description: A human-readable explanation specific to this occurrence of the problem.
